The paper deals with approximation algorithms for a graph theory problem, specifically the minimum unweighted Vertex Cover problem with Hard Capacity constraints (VCHC) on f-hypergraphs. This problem is related to several subfields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), graph theory (cs.GT), computational complexity (cs.CC), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational geometry (cs.CG). Given that the paper focuses on approximation algorithms and iterative rounding techniques, cs.DS and cs.CG are less likely sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CC, cs.DM, and cs.CG, in that order.
